The order of 7 parameters of the USER's function HEAT CONDUCTIVITY 
at time TEMPS, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the S (SURFACE if 2d OBJECT) or V (VOLUME if 3d OBJECT) or O (OBJECT)
of type number NO_TYPE_SVO (3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT)
the directory number NO_SVO
for a temperature TEMPER, known or unknown
the NUCOEF number of the ANISOTROPIC CONDUCTIVITY COEFFICIENT
1:C11, 2:C12=C21, 3:C22, 4:C13=C31, 5:C23=C32, 6:C33
must be

CONDUCTIVITY( TEMPS, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_SVO, NO_SVO, TEMPER, NUCOEF ) 

and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized during its call.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of CONDUCTIVITY.
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc conductivity( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material, temper, nuc ) ;
if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'steel' )
then if nuc=1 then
        conductivity= 20;
     else
        if nuc=2 then
	   conductivity= 20;
        endif;
     endif;
else if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'copper' )
     then conductivity=52;
     else conductivity=0 ;
     endif;  
endif;
endfunc; 

Remark: the LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.
